## 15. Script completo de restore

Crie um arquivo chamado:

```bash
restore-keyvault.sh
```

Conteúdo:

```bash
#!/bin/bash

set -euo pipefail

SUBSCRIPTION_ID="<subscription-id>"
TARGET_VAULT="<key-vault-destino>"
BACKUP_DIR="./keyvault-backup"

echo "Selecionando subscription..."
az account set --subscription "$SUBSCRIPTION_ID"

echo "Iniciando restore de secrets..."
for file in "$BACKUP_DIR/secrets/"*.bak; do
  [ -e "$file" ] || continue

  echo "Restore secret: $file"

  az keyvault secret restore \
    --vault-name "$TARGET_VAULT" \
    --file "$file"
done

echo "Iniciando restore de keys..."
for file in "$BACKUP_DIR/keys/"*.bak; do
  [ -e "$file" ] || continue

  echo "Restore key: $file"

  az keyvault key restore \
    --vault-name "$TARGET_VAULT" \
    --file "$file"
done

echo "Iniciando restore de certificates..."
for file in "$BACKUP_DIR/certificates/"*.bak; do
  [ -e "$file" ] || continue

  echo "Restore certificate: $file"

  az keyvault certificate restore \
    --vault-name "$TARGET_VAULT" \
    --file "$file"
done

echo "Restore finalizado com sucesso."
```

Dar permissão de execução:

```bash
